
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Andromeda_Information";
}

<div class="container white-txt larger-font dark-bkr">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-1"></div>
        <div class="col-lg-10">
            <h1 class="info-page-title text-center">ANDROMEDA GALAXY INFORMATION</h1>
            <br />
            <div>
                <h2>The Andromeda Galaxy</h2>
                <p class="info-par">
                    The Andromeda Galaxy is the closest spiral galaxy to our Milky Way Galaxy.
                    It also goes by the names M31 or Messier 31. [<a href="https://www.space.com/15590-andromeda-galaxy-m31.html">REF</a>]
                </p>
            </div>
            <br />
            <div>
                <h2>Discovery</h2>
                <p class="info-par">
                    The other names come from Charles Messier who wrote about the galaxy that he thought was a nebula. [<a href="https://www.space.com/16686-charles-messier-biography.html">REF</a>]
                    Edwin Hubble in the 1920s discovered that Andromeda was much larger than originally thought and helped reclassify Andromeda as a galaxy.
                    This started the idea that the universe is filled with more galaxies than just the Milky Way. [<a href="https://apod.nasa.gov/apod/ap960406.html">REF</a>]
                </p>
            </div>
            <br />
            <div>
                <h2>Distance</h2>
                <p class="info-par">
                    Andromeda is 2.5 million lightyears away. [<a href="https://www.space.com/15590-andromeda-galaxy-m31.html">REF</a>]
                    The Andromeda Galaxy has an apparent magnitude(brightness) of 3.6 so it is bright enough to be visible from Earth. [<a href="https://astronomy.swin.edu.au/cms/astro/cosmos/A/Andromeda+galaxy">REF</a>]
                </p>
            </div>
            <br />
            <div>
                <h2>Andromeda and the Milky Way</h2>
                <p class="info-par">
                    The Andromeda Galaxy is around 222,000 light years across more than double your Milky Way Galaxy at 100,000 light years across. [<a href="https://www.universetoday.com/22821/the-milky-way-and-andromeda/">REF</a>]
                    Andromeda also has a higher amount of stars at around 1 trillion stars compared to the around 200-400 billion in the Milky Way. [<a href="http://annesastronomynews.com/photo-gallery-ii/galaxies-clusters/the-andromeda-galaxy-m31/">REF</a>]
                </p>
            </div>
            <br />
            <div>
                <h2>The Future of Andromeda</h2>
                <p class="info-par">
                    The Andromeda Galaxy will one day collide with the Milky Way Galaxy. It is estimated that it will happen in around 4 billion years and they will completely merge in around 6 billion years.
                    This is something that is common with many galaxies and both the Milky Way and Andromeda show signs of having collided with other galaxies before.[<a href="https://www.space.com/15590-andromeda-galaxy-m31.html">REF</a>]
                </p>
            </div>
            <br />
            <div>
                <h2>Interesting Facts about The Andromeda Galaxy</h2>
                <p class="info-par">
                    In 2017 it was discovered that the Andromeda Galaxy contained two different black holes.
                    These were special as they orbit each other at a distance that may only be a couple 100 times the distance between the Earth and Sun.
                    Because they are relatively close the two black holes will eventually merge in anywhere from 350 to 360,000 years. [<a href="https://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/chandra/news/giant-black-hole-pair-photobombs-andromeda-galaxy.html">REF</a>]
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-1"></div>
    </div>
</div>


<br />
<br />
<br />

<h1 style="color: white; text-align: center">User Comments</h1>

@if (Model != null)
{
    foreach (var item in Model)
    {
        <div class="container information-paragraphs dark-bkr" style="border: 1px solid white; width: 50%">
            <div id="usernameDateBox">
                <p>@item.Username || @item.PostDate.ToShortDateString()</p>
            </div>

            <div id="userCommentBox">
                <p>@item.Comment</p>
            </div>

            @if (User.Identity.IsAuthenticated)
            {
                <img src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0UfhaE3CMHM/hqdefault.jpg" style="width: 24px; height: 18px;" />
                @Html.ActionLink("Report", "ReportComment", new { id = item.Id, returnURL = "Andromeda_Information" })
                <img src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/0UfhaE3CMHM/hqdefault.jpg" style="width: 24px; height: 18px;" />
            }
        </div>
        <br />
    }
}

<br />
<br />
<br />

@if (User.Identity.IsAuthenticated)
{
    <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; height: 100%;">
        <form>
            <label for="commentBox" style="color: white">Type your comment. (1000 character limit)</label><br />
            <textarea id="commentBox" maxlength="1000" style=" width: 100%; height: 150px; padding: 12px 20px; box-sizing: border-box; border: 2px solid #ccc; border-radius: 4px; background-color: #f8f8f8; font-size: 16px; resize: none; color: black;"></textarea>

            <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; height: 100%;">
                <button type="button" onclick="submitComment('@ViewBag.URL')" style="color: black;">Submit Your Comment</button>
            </div>
        </form>
    </div>


}
else
{
    <div class="information-paragraphs dark-bkr" style="margin-left: 30%; width: 40%; text-align: center">
        <h2>Please @Html.ActionLink("log in", "Login", "Account") to post a comment!</h2>
    </div>
}

<script src="~/Scripts/main.js"></script>